 <p>Extended Life Coolant (ELC) is a type of coolant used in automotive and heavy-duty diesel engines. It is formulated to have an extended service life compared to traditional coolants, typically lasting up to 5 years or 150,000 miles. ELC contains organic acid technology (OAT) or other additives that provide corrosion protection and help maintain engine efficiency over longer intervals between coolant changes.</p>
 
 
 
 <p><strong>Demand Drivers</strong>: Growth in the Extended Life Coolant market is driven by increasing adoption in automotive and industrial applications, where these coolants offer longer service intervals and better engine protection.</p>
